3 Priests and 3 devils Puzzle

Six people — 3 Priests and 3 Devils — need to cross a river using a boat that holds at most two people.

Rules:

At any time (on either riverbank or in the boat), if the number of Devils exceeds the number of Priests, the Devils will eat the Priests (i.e., that situation is forbidden).
The boat requires at least one person to move (it cannot move empty).
You may make as many crossings as needed, but must always avoid forbidden states.
Get all 6 people safely to the other side of the river without ever allowing the Devils to outnumber the Priests on either bank.

Solution:

To safely get all 3 priests and 3 devils to the other side of the river without ever leaving more devils than priests on either side, follow these 6 steps:

The boat can carry only two people at a time. At no point should devils outnumber priests on either riverbank.

Step 1: One priest and one devil cross the river.

The devil stays, and the priest returns with the boat.
Step 2: Two devils cross the river.

One devil stays, and the other returns with the boat.
Now, 2 devils are on the far side; 3 priests and 1 devil are on the starting side.
Step 3: Two priests cross the river.

One priest stays, and the other returns with 1 devil.
Step 4: The remaining two priests cross the river.

Now, 3 priests and 1 devil are on the far side; 2 devils are on the starting side.
One devil returns with the boat.
Step 5: Two devils cross the river.

One devil stays, and the other returns with the boat.
Step 6: The last two devils cross together.

All 3 priests and 3 devils are now safely on the far side.
